{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Wound Level Effects\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Stunned:} \u8722 ?1D for all remaining actions this round and next round.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Wounded:} \u8722 ?1D to all actions until healed.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Severely Wounded:} \u8722 ?2D on all actions until healed.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Incapacitated:} As a free action before losing consciousness, the character may try to stay up with a Moderate (15) {\i Stamina} roll. If successful, he may continue to act, but with a \u8722 ?3D penalty. If he fails, he is knocked out for 10D minutes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Mortally Wounded:} The character is near death and knocked unconscious with no chance to keep up. Roll the character's Might each round, the character finally dies if the roll is less than the number of minutes he's been at this level.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Dead:} The character has perished.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Vehicles\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 All vehicles from ancient chariots to futuristic starships are defined by a common set of statistics. The following stats help the GM and players quickly resolve all actions related to vehicles.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Skill:} What skill is used to drive/pilot it.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Scale:} The size of the vehicle.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Body:} Used to resist damage.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Maneuverability (MNV):} How easy it is to handle. This gives a bonus on {\i Drive} and {\i Pilot} skill rolls.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Move:} How fast it can travel.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Crew:} The number needed to successfully operate the vehicle.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Passengers (Psg):} Non-crew capacity.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Weapons:} Any armaments mounted on the vehicle.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Cargo:} How much stuff it can carry.\par}
