{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Effects of Damage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Maneuverability:} Each time this is affected the vehicle loses 1D. This can go negative becoming a penalty to the driver's skill roll.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b System Damaged:} Randomly select a vehicle's system and it either becomes broken or loses 1D from its rating (if applicable). Examples include communications/radio, sensors, shielding, sail, rigging, armor, etc.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Structural Damage:} The vehicle receives one wound level. Treat these like character wound levels. Mortally wounded vehicles stop running and Dead vehicles are considered destroyed.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Ramming\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When vehicles are at short range, a pursuer may try to ram. To successfully ram the pilot needs to roll higher than the target's {\i Pilot} skill check. If successful both vehicles take damage equal to to the body of attacking plus relative move dice.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Multiple Weapons on Vehicles\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When vehicles have more than one weapon of a single type, they can be fired as a single salvo. This requires a successful {\i Command} skill roll with the difficulty based on the number of guns being combined. Each doubling of the number of weapons combined increases the damage by one pip.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Chases\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When attempting to overtake or outrun an opponent the GM determines what range you are at (Short/Medium/Long). Each turn each vehicle makes a {\i Drive/Pilot} check, with the vehicle's Move dice granting a bonus. The higher roll either closes or increases the distance 1 range as desired. If reduced below Short you catch up, if increased beyond Long you escape.\par}
