{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 The Simple Magic System\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Call it Ki, Chi, Sorcery, Latent Psi, etc; it's all just different flavors of magic. Magic lets you break the rules of the universe in creative ways. Some games let you use flashy spells; others require you to use more subtle effects. Speak with your GM about the limits of magic in his game.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Access to Magic\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In some games, none may use magic, in others everyone can. The most common option is a middle ground that requires the character to start the game with the Sorcerer esoteric perk.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Casting Spells\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 All spells have a target number (TN) listed in their description. Sorcerers roll {\i Magic} to determine success. Only one spell may be cast per turn. Success on the roll mean the spell is cast, see each spell description for the exact effect achieved. On a failed roll, the Sorcerer suffers a \u8722 ?1D penalty to their {\i Magic} skill. Further failures increase the penalty. One hour of rest with no interruption removes all penalties.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Spells Requiring Multiple Actions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Some spells require additional actions to be taken after casting. For example, thrown spells require the Sorcerer to cast the spell and then hit the target by making a {\i Throwing} skill check. The Sorcerer may wait until the next turn to throw the spell or they may opt to suffer the penalty for multiple actions and do them all in one turn.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Concentration (CONC)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Some spells require the Sorcerer to maintain concentration for the spell to remain in effect. Each spell maintained counts as one action.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Beginning Spells & Learning More\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The character knows two spells for each die allocated to {\i Magic} at character creation. Learning a new spell costs 2 CP.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Magic Perks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Characters that are able to learn the {\i Magic} skill may also purchase the following Perks.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Familiar (1):} The character has an imp for a companion. The familiar can fly at a rate of 60 ft each turn, can talk, and has 1D in each attribute. He also has 3D in skills. He can't cast spells, but he can turn into a black cat or other small animal at will.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Totem Spirit (1):} The character has a spiritual advisor that speaks to him in his dreams or visions. This spirit will likely have a somewhat alien perspective on matters, and certainly won't always just tell the character everything he knows. Totem Spirits employ riddles, puzzles, and enjoy sending the character off on ridiculous quests; but they also have insight and know things man was never meant to know.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Magic Complications\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The GM may also allow special complications for magic capable characters.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Demonic Pact:} The character has allied himself with a demon. It tends to impress all the wrong people. You earn bonus CP any time this complicates your life.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b White Wizard:} You can't harm anyone with your magic. Ever. Earn 1 bonus CP every session.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Sorcerer's Tools\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Some special enchanted items are of use only to those capable of using spells. Activating the bonus granted by an item does not count as an action. When found a sorcerer must attune the item before he can use it. This requires the passing of three days while keeping the item close.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Cloak} grants +2D to the {\i Magic} skill test required to use the Fly and Teleport spells.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Crystal Ball} grants +3D to the {\i Magic} skill test required to use the Clairvoyance and Divination spells.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Magic Wand} grants +1D to any {\i Magic} skill test when used for the spell the wand was designed for.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Spell Staff} grants +1D to {\i Magic} once each day.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Making Sorcerer's Tools\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Sorcerers may construct their own tools; this requires time, money, and CP. During the construction of the item the sorcerer must work for twelve hours each day. If any days are skipped all effort is lost. At the end of the process he rolls a {\i Magic} check vs. the TN listed below. If he fails all effort and money is wasted but no CP were spent.\par}
