{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Clairvoyance\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 23, Duration: Concentration, Range: 300 feet, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The caster's senses leave his own body and project outward to any point within 300 feet. The caster may move the area he perceives at the rate of 10 feet per turn. While in this state, he cannot take any physical action and any damage done to him will end the spell.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Conjure Elemental\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 31, Duration: Permanent, Range: Zero, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Sorcerers may summon only one elemental per day by using this spell. The caster also needs a large quantity of the type of element on hand they wish to conjure. For example, a bonfire for a fire elemental or a well for a water elemental. Controlling the elemental requires use of the {\i Command} skill. Uncontrolled elementals will attack everyone, including the conjurer.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Control Weather\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 35, Duration: Concentration, Range: \u189 ? mile radius\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The caster dictates the weather in the area affected. He can make it hot, cold, snowy, rainy, foggy, or calm as desired.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Curse\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 15 + Resist Roll, Duration: Permanent, Range: Touch, Resisted: Charm\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The target of this spell suffers some negative effect determined by the caster. Examples include being struck mute until hearing a certain word, deafness or blindness, inability to run or cross running water. This spell is open ended but the GM has final say on all effects. {\i Dispel Magic} will remove any curse.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Dark Vision\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 23, Duration: 1 hour, Range: Touch, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The target can see 60 feet in the dark.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Death Spell\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 35, Duration: Instant, Range: 30 feet, Resisted: Special\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If successfully cast, the Sorcerer rolls his {\i Magic} skill without his Wit attribute for damage. The target resists using only Might. For example, Melkot casts {\i Death Spell} on Tamore. Melkot has a Wit of 4D and 10D in {\i Magic}. Melkot would roll 6D for damage (10D \u8211- 4D) and Tamore would resist with his Might.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Dispel Magic\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: Special, Duration: Permanent, Range: 30 feet, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The caster undoes any single spell or permanent magical effect. The target number is five higher than the spell or effect being targeted. Some things cannot be dispelled, such as healing and resurrection.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Divination\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: Special, Duration: Concentration, Range: Self, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Sorcerer can attempt to see the future or the past. The immediate future or past normally has a TN of 25 while more distant events have a higher TN. For instance, seeing a year into the future may have a TN of 45 while a year into the past is only 35. If attempting to divine about specific objects or people that are not present, the difficulty goes up by 10 or more depending on closeness of relationship to the Sorcerer.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Earthquake\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 39, Duration: 1 round, Range: 200 feet, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 An intense tremor rips the ground in a 50 foot radius from the chosen epicenter. This collapses structures, opens cracks in the ground, and more. While the effect lasts creatures on the ground cannot move, attack, or cast spells. Any creature caught inside a collapsing structure must resist 6D damage.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 ESP\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 15 + Resist Roll, Duration: Concentration, Range: 50 feet, Resisted: Charm\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When cast you can hear the thoughts of any one person; language is no barrier.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Fly\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 23 (or 15), Duration: Concentration, Range: Self, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 While maintained the Sorcerer can fly at a rate of 90 feet per round. If the spell ends before landing the character will float to the ground. The character may hover and carry up to his own weight aloft. If the character only wishes to levitate vertically the TN of the spell is 15.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Growth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 23 + Special, Duration: 10 Rounds, Range: Self, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The caster grows. Each scale increase adds +10 to the TN. For example, for a human sorcerer to grow to the size of a dragon would require 2 scale increases making the TN 43.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Hasten\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 23, Duration: 5 rounds, Range: touch, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Targets have their multiple action penalty reduced by 1D. The effects of multiple Hasten spells don't stack.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Heal\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: Special, Duration: Instant, Range: Touch, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Sorcerer must concentrate for 6 turns before casting this spell. The TN is 15 when attempting to heal anyone wounded or severely wounded, 19 for incapacitated characters, and 23 for the mortally wounded. Success reduces the wound level by one. If {\i Heal} is used more than once per day on a target, the target number of additional castings increases by +10.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Illusions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: Special + Resist Roll, Duration: Concentration, Range: 50 foot radius, Resisted: Wit\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Illusions create false perceptions in the minds of the effected. The target number is 15 plus 2 per person after the first targeted plus their individual Resist Roll. Compare results for each person individually to see if they are affected. GMs may wish to roll for the highest Resist first and if they fail consider all to have failed.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Invisibility\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 27, Duration: 1 hour, Range: Touch, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This spell renders the target almost unseen granting a +5D bonus to {\i Stealth}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Light\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 15, Duration: 1 hour, Range: 100 feet, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The targeted location or object glows as brightly as a torch.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Lightning Bolt\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 23, Duration: Instant, Range: 150 feet, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The caster throws lightning. This requires the use of the {\i Throwing} skill. If the caster attempts to throw it the same round it is cast the multiple action penalty applies to both the casting and throwing of the spell. The caster may also choose to throw the lightning the round after casting to avoid the penalty. However if he waits any longer the effect dissipates. Targets may make a {\i Dodge} roll to avoid being hit. A successful hit inflicts 5D damage. Armor does not protect against {\i Lightning Bolt}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Paralysis\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 15 + Resist Roll, Duration: 1 hour, Range: 150, Resisted: Might\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The target becomes paralyzed, freezing in place.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Petrify\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 25 + Resist Roll, Duration: Permanent, Range: 100 feet, Resisted: Might\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Turns one creature into a statue include all gear and any items held. {\i Dispel Magic} will return the target to their normal state.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Possession\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 25 + Resist Roll, Duration: Concentration (special), Range: 500 feet, Resisted: Charm\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The sorcerer takes control of the physical body of a single character or creature. The sorcerer may make the possessed being take any physical action it is capable of, but can't make it use {\i Magic} or any Perk. The possessed being uses its own Might and Agility, but skills depend on those of the sorcerer. The possessed may contest the sorcerer for control each round.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Resist Elements\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 19, Duration: 1 hour, Range: 30 feet, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When cast, the Sorcerer selects one element such as fire, cold, or electricity, and the target is granted a +1D bonus to resist damage from that source.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Resurrection\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 60, Duration: Permanent, Range: touch, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A body which has been dead for less than one month may be restored to life; but no one who has died from old age can be raised. Whether or not the casting of this spell is successful the Sorcerer's {\i Magic} skill is reduced by 3D for one day.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 See Magic Aura\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 15, Duration: Concentration, Range: 30 feet, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The caster can see a magical glow on anything enchanted.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Shape Change\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 15, Duration: Concentration, Range: 30 feet, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The caster transforms into any creature (not specific individuals) gaining its physical attributes. Spells may not be cast while changed. The TN is increased by +10 per increase in scale.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Slumber\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 10 + Resist Roll, Duration: 1 hour, Range: 30 foot radius, Resisted: Wit\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Sorcerer can affect as many targets as he has dice in {\i Magic}. Targets resist individually, falling into a deep sleep on failure.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Still Mind\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 43, Duration: Concentration, Range: Self, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Sorcerer is protected from all spells that influence, detect, or read emotions and thoughts.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Telekinesis\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: 31 + Special, Duration: Concentration, Range: 150 Feet, Resisted: None / Might\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The caster moves up to 50 lbs per die in {\i Magic} up to 30 feet per round. Living beings may resist using Might.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Teleport\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TN: Special, Duration: Instant, Range: 10 foot radius, Resisted: None\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Sorcerers instantly transport themselves or other beings to a designated destination at any distance. Unwilling subjects cannot be teleported. The base TN is 30 for one target, plus 5 more for each additional target. A caster may not teleport to any place he has not seen before.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Enchanted Items\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Scrolls\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 These are written spells nearly ready to cast. They allow a caster who doesn't know a spell to use it once before it burns to ash. The character must be able to use spells to read a scroll.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Potions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Distilled arcane power. The magic is released when consumed.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b A Potion of Healing} automatically heals a single wound level.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b A Potion of Skill} grant's +2D to a selected skill for ten minutes. A different variant of the potion exists for each skill.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b A Potion of Changing} will {\i Shape Change} the character into any one predetermined form. The effect lasts one hour.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Enchanted Arms and Armor\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 These grant a bonus or have a unique effect when wielded.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Axe of Dwarf Mercy} deals an additional +1D damage when striking Goblins or Orcs.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Valiant Sword} grants its wielder an additional +1D to {\i Command} allied troops.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Shield of Faith} grants its wielder +1D to resist any magic.\par}
